# Test fixtures and snapshots are byte-offset-sensitive: the lexer/parser golden snapshots record
# absolute start/end offsets computed from the fixture text, so a CRLF checkout (core.autocrlf on
# Windows) shifts every offset and fails the suite. Force LF so every platform checks out the same
# bytes the snapshots were recorded from.
*.rules text eol=lf
*.shader text eol=lf
*.snap text eol=lf
